But the original had `if (child == first) return null;` without first null check. So if first is null and child is null, it returns null. If first is null and child is non-null, it will go to loop and NPE. So my fix adds `first == null` check. That is a minimal fix.

Now for `findAliases`, I'll add a null check for `parent`? Actually, in the else if (isVar) branch, there is `grandparent = parent.getParent()`. If parent is root, grandparent could be null. But parent is a VAR node, which should not be root. So safe.

I'll leave `findAliases` as is.

